#Text=On December 13 , 2016 , Long Island Press reported that local authorities have positively identified skeletal remains ( formerly referred to as  Jane Doe 3 " ) found at Jones Beach State Park in 2011 as belonging to Peaches .

column1: #Text=Remains of a child were also found in 2011 , east of Cedar Beach , with DNA testing identifying Jane Doe 3 -- or " Peaches " — as its mother .
#Text=As a result of these findings , Peaches has now been linked to the Long Island serial killer as a potential early victim . [ 6 ]
#Text=Related cases
#Text=" Cherries "
#Text=Tattoo worn by " Cherries "
#Text=On March 3 , 2007 a dismembered torso was found in a suitcase in Harbor Island Park in Mamaroneck , Westchester County , New York . [ 7 ]
#Text=Investigators believe the victim was a heavy-set Hispanic or light-skinned African-American woman , about five feet seven inches tall , and one-hundred eighty to two-hundred pounds .
#Text=She had a tattoo of two red cherries on a green stem located on her right breast . [ 8 ]
#Text=" Cherries " ( as she is referred to by law enforcement ) was also decapitated and dismembered , although her original cause of death was a stab wound to the torso . [ 9 ]
#Text=Unlike Peaches , investigators found both of Cherries ' legs , which washed up on the shore of Cablevision owner James Dolan 's beachfront estate in Oyster Bay , New York .
#Text=Inside the suitcase investigators found a pair of gray Champion sweat pants , a tan or cream-colored long-sleeved shirt by Voice and a red camisole bearing Spanish-language labels .
#Text=The dark blue or black suitcase is sold exclusively at Wal-Mart stores .
#Text=Police also found small scraps of paper tucked away in the crevices of the suitcase .
#Text=When pieced together , it looks like a calendar with the Spanish word " cinco " and the phrase " begin to live .
